<item>
            <title>[SPARK-30657] Streaming limit after streaming dropDuplicates can throw error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-30657</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;LocalLimitExec&lt;/tt&gt; does not consume the iterator of the child plan. So if there is a limit after a stateful operator like streaming dedup in append mode (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;streamingdf.dropDuplicates().limit(5&lt;/tt&gt;)), the state changes of streaming duplicate may not be committed (most stateful ops commit state changes only after the generated iterator is fully consumed). This leads to the next batch failing with &lt;tt&gt;java.lang.IllegalStateException: Error reading delta file .../N.delta does not exist&lt;/tt&gt; as the state store delta file was never generated.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
